Issue #1 — Initial Repository Setup: Structure, Licensing, and Publication
This issue tracks the initial setup and publication of the Oscie Coherence Architecture research repository, including structure, licensing, and core documentation.
Tasks Completed
Added root repository structure
Added README.md with project overview, paper summary, and citation info
Added LICENSE (Apache 2.0)
Added .gitignore (Python template + research file ignores)
Uploaded preprint PDF (paper/Oscie_CI_Pub.pdf)
Added placeholder directories for examples/ and figures/
Added metadata files (abstract.md, citation.bib)
Next Steps
Add coherence evaluation protocol to /examples/
Add preliminary diagrams to /figures/ (UCD, CUE, VE+ stack)
Set up versioned “Releases” for v1.0 of the paper
(Optional) Register Zenodo DOI for permanent citation
Purpose
This establishes the repo as the canonical public reference for the Oscie Coherence Architecture, UCD framework, ACI stack, CUE stability engine, VE+ energy layer, and baseline Coherence Capacity benchmark.
